name: io.bytes.per.checksum
description:
The number of bytes per checksum.  Must not be larger than
  io.file.buffer.size.

name: dfs.client.refresh.read-block-locations.threads
description:
Number of threads to use for refreshing LocatedBlocks of registered
      DFSInputStreams. If a DFSClient opens many DFSInputStreams, increasing
      this may help refresh them all in a timely manner.

name: dfs.edit.log.transfer.timeout
description:
Socket timeout for edit log transfer in milliseconds. This timeout
    should be configured such that normal edit log transfer for journal
    node syncing can complete successfully.

name: fs.s3a.connection.establish.timeout
description: Socket connection setup timeout in milliseconds.

name: mapreduce.task.exit.timeout
description:
The number of milliseconds before a task will be
  terminated if it stays in finishing state for too long.
  After a task attempt completes from TaskUmbilicalProtocol's point of view,
  it will be transitioned to finishing state. That will give a chance for the
  task to exit by itself.

name: ftp.client-write-packet-size
description: Packet size for clients to write

name: dfs.client.deadnode.detection.probe.deadnode.threads
description: The maximum number of threads to use for probing dead node.

name: mapreduce.map.cpu.vcores
description:
The number of virtual cores to request from the scheduler for
  each map task.

name: mapreduce.task.userlog.limit.kb
description: The maximum size of user-logs of each task in KB. 0 disables the cap.
